{
  "texts": [
    "HallucinationsOur experiments defined standard, community-accepted phenotype concept recognition tasks and the evaluation targeted HPO IDs extracted by the models.",
    "Hence, in terms of hallucinations.",
    "(inaccurate, nonsensical, or irrelevant output given the given context), the expectation was to find nonexisting HPO IDs in the output produced by the models.",
    "We observed an insignificant number of hallucinations (Table 4), and as such, hallucinations do not pose a challenge for this task.",
    "Some examples of hallucinations include: HP:0020115, HP:0025111, HP:0023656, HP:0031966, HP:0020019, HP:0040060."
  ]
}